# Exercise 6.5 — Deliberately divergent.
#
# Uncomment the divergent rule and run with --backend native. It
# will spin until you interrupt it (Ctrl-C). Then add a bound.

counter(0).
# Divergent — no upper bound on N. Each iteration extends the
# active domain by one new integer.
# TODO: uncomment the next rule and run; it will not terminate.
# counter(N + 1) :- counter(N).

# TODO: then add a bound like `N < 1000` to the body to restore
# termination.

?- counter(N).
